dct_title_s: Carte générale de la division administrative de la Turquie d'Asie  / par Vital Cuinet ; éditieur Ernest Leroux.
dct_description_sm: This general map is considered an introduction to the name "Tukey d' Asia", a name relative new for Asia Minor or Anatolia. Principal meridian is Paris. Ancillary map: Hedjaz et Yemen. Includes Index: "Division administrative (d'aprés le  "Salnameh" official de 1306) : vilayets, sandjaks, & cazas". Map shows administrative boundaries (vilayet, sandjaks, cazas). Original map is filed in the Map/Geospatial Center, a map reproduction is attached to companion volume.
